uses:

A module is a reusable group of Terraform resources


# reuse same module for dev and prod
module "dev_ec2" {
  source        = "./modules/ec2"
  name          = "dev-ec2"
  instance_type = "t3.micro"
  ami_id        = "ami-123456"
  key_name      = "dev-key"
}

module "prod_ec2" {
  source        = "./modules/ec2"
  name          = "prod-ec2"
  instance_type = "t3.large"
  ami_id        = "ami-123456"
  key_name      = "prod-key"
}


With module    → write once, call multiple times with different values

Yes, two separate EC2 instances:
Same module, different values — no need to rewrite the EC2 resource twice.

dev_ec2  → t3.micro  , name = "dev-ec2"
prod_ec2 → t3.large  , name = "prod-ec2"

